TY  - JOUR
T1  - Algorithms for Scheduling a Single Machine to Minimize the Weighted Number of Late Jobs
AU  - Potts, C. N.
AU  - Van Wassenhove, L. N.
Y1  - 1988/07/01
PY  - 1988
DA  - 1988/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.34.7.843
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.34.7.843
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 843
EP  - 858
VL  - 34
IS  - 7
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper considers the problem of scheduling n jobs, each having a processing time, a due date and a weight, on a single machine to minimize the weighted number of late jobs. An O(n log n) algorithm is given for solving the linear programming problem obtained by relaxing the integrality constraints in a zero-one programming formulation of the problem. This linear programming lower bound is used in a reduction algorithm that eliminates jobs from the problem. Also, a branch and bound algorithm that uses the linear programming lower bound is proposed. Computational results with branch and bound algorithms that use this and other lower bounds and with a dynamic programming algorithm for problems with up to 1000 jobs are given.
AB  - This paper considers the problem of scheduling n jobs, each having a processing time, a due date and a weight, on a single machine to minimize the weighted number of late jobs. An O(n log n) algorithm is given for solving the linear programming problem obtained by relaxing the integrality constraints in a zero-one programming formulation of the problem. This linear programming lower bound is used in a reduction algorithm that eliminates jobs from the problem. Also, a branch and bound algorithm that uses the linear programming lower bound is proposed. Computational results with branch and bound algorithms that use this and other lower bounds and with a dynamic programming algorithm for problems with up to 1000 jobs are given.
